        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16892",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As this is database specific it would be best that each adapter know what date\/time format he wants to have.\n\nThe handling within Zend_Date is quite easy...\n\n{code}\n$date = new Zend_Date($format, $dbformat);\n$databasevalue = $date->toString($dbformat);\n{code}\n\nBut also to mention...\nThe fastest way would be to have all dates extracted as unix timestamp from the database...\nEach database also accepts timestamps as input for datetime fields.\nThis would mean that no parsing has to occur which would make the code much faster.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-21T15:08:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-21T15:08:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16939",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevecrozz",
                        "name": "stevecrozz",
                        "displayName": "Stephen Crosby",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Additionally, it would be very handy to allow Zend_Db to automatically adjust incoming and outgoing Zend_Date objects for database-specific date object fields, and also automatically adjust them to GMT and back.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevecrozz",
                        "name": "stevecrozz",
                        "displayName": "Stephen Crosby",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-24T14:44:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-24T14:44:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16980",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
